# Why this works: bounded queues turn 'one slow stage bricks the stream'
# into observable backpressure; batched embedding amortises GPU cost;
# idempotency keys make a replay safe even if the consumer crashed mid-
# batch; stage-tagged dead-letter makes 'what stage is dropping events'
# answerable from the dashboard.
